STEP 1- INTRODUCTION (0:00 – 0:30)


Landing Page

“Hello, today I’m presenting my project Bizora. It is a full-stack entrepreneur networking platform where founders, investors, and mentors can connect, share ideas, host events, and collaborate.”

STEP 2- PROBLEM STATEMENT (0:30 – 1:00)

Slowly scroll landing page
Highlight Ideas, Events, Collaborate

“Many entrepreneurs struggle to find the right mentors, investors, and collaborators in one place. Existing platforms are fragmented. Bizora solves this by providing a single integrated platform.”

STEP 3 AUTHENTICATION FLOW (1:00 – 1:30)

Click Login
Enter credentials
Login success → redirect

“Bizora uses secure authentication with JWT and protected routes. After login, users are redirected to a personalized dashboard.”

Role-based users

STEP 4- DASHBOARD OVERVIEW (1:30 – 2:30) 

Dashboard page
Scroll slowly top → bottom

“This is the main dashboard. It provides a complete overview of user activity.”

Posts count
Likes
Events
Unread messages (red indicator)
Latest posts preview
Upcoming events (date-based)
Unread messages section
Admin panel

STEP 5- POSTS & COMMENTS (2:30 – 3:15)

Click Posts / Feed

Open a post
Scroll comments
Add a comment

“Users can create posts, share ideas, and interact through comments. Comments support edit and delete for owners, and the UI is chat-style for readability.”

Latest posts logic
Profile picture display
Clean comment UI

STEP 6- EVENTS MODULE (3:15 – 4:00)

Events list
Open event detail
Click Going / Interested

“The events module allows users to create and join meetups, workshops, and webinars. Events are filtered by date, and organizers can edit or delete their events.”

Online / Offline / Hybrid
Date-based filtering

STEP 7- MESSAGING SYSTEM (4:00 – 4:45)

Messages page
Unread chat
Send a message

“Bizora includes a direct messaging system with unread message tracking and a clean chat interface. The system is scalable for real-time communication.”

Unread message count
Auto scroll
Chat bubbles

STEP 8- PROFILE MANAGEMENT (4:45 – 5:30)

Profile page
Edit profile
Change avatar

“Each user has a profile page where they can update their information, skills, and profile image. Editing is handled on the same route for better user experience.”

Single route edit

Avatar upload

Public profile view

STEP 9- ADMIN SUPPORT PANEL (5:30 – 6:00)

Dashboard bottom
Admin cards
Click Contact Admin

“The dashboard includes an admin support panel. Users can contact administrators directly using the system’s default mail application.”


STEP 10- TECH STACK & ARCHITECTURE (6:00 – 6:40)

Project folder structure
Backend routes
MongoDB models

“Bizora is built using the MERN stack—MongoDB, Express, React, and Node—with Tailwind CSS for UI. The backend follows RESTful architecture with secure APIs.”

STEP 11- CONCLUSION (6:40 – 7:00)

Dashboard again
Smooth scroll

“Bizora provides a scalable and user-friendly platform for entrepreneurial networking. Future improvements include real-time notifications and analytics.”